basics.name: Jessica Collins
basics.label: Web Developer
basics.summary: An accomplished IT professional with an extensive background in software development processes and systems operations. Deeply dedicated to refocusing career towards software development while effectively utilizing existing skill set.

work.summary: Responsibilities primarily consisted of supporting the Administrative Office of the US Courts’ software quality assurance test center.
highlights: Intranet portal web development using Drupal / LAMP technologies

work.summary: Responsibilities primarily consisted of testing cloud storage, web based email, and calendar applications on a fast paced, agile software development team.
highlights: Implemented functional, automated, mobile, and security test processes
Interpret business requirement, write test cases, report defects, and author test reports
Compose customer facing help articles and maintain knowledge base WIKI
Selected to mentor Jr. QA Engineers through the company’s pilot Jr. Developer program

work.summary: Responsibilities primarily consisted of testing web applications for the US Courts.
highlights: Functional and automated testing across multiple platforms for several projects
Hosted national clients onsite to participate in user acceptance testing
Compose customer facing help articles and maintain knowledge base WIKI
Selected to be a test lead, which included managing assignments, task delegation, and project scheduling

work.summary: Solely implemented industry standard software quality assurance methodologies for a start up company that developed a full-featured web application designed to facilitate the management of service industry companies.
Employed in depth troubleshooting techniques to resolve dedicated client issues related to B2B E-Commerce transactions for large national clients. Provided rotating, on call 24/7 support.
Applied standard mainframe operating procedures including managing programs, systems monitoring, and data library management.
Developed dynamic web pages using HTML, CSS, and PHP for an embedded systems design web application in an intense start up environment.
Linux systems administration, network configuration, and technical support for a local Internet service provider.
Mainframe operation, media library management and repair for a national pharmaceutical data warehousing and analysis company.

volunteer.summary: Wheelchair Labs improves the lives of those who are mobility impaired by repairing and refurbishing used electric wheelchairs and scooters, and donating them to those in need.
